 MAVEN - build automation tool.
 For testers it used:

 1. Create a project sturcture (test/java --> java related code
                                test/resources --> resources we used to test
 2. manage project dependencies
 pom.xml - configuration file for maven projects

maven.apache.org == > here we can read all about Maven

compiler = tells us which Java version we use
 <properties>
        <maven.compiler.source>1.8</maven.compiler.source>
        <maven.compiler.target>1.8</maven.compiler.target>
    </properties>


io.github.bonigarcia  = automatically updates google or firefox version
<dependency>
            <groupId>io.github.bonigarcia</groupId>
            <artifactId>webdrivermanager</artifactId>
            <version>4.2.2</version>
        </dependency>

     Target folder == > will store all the outcomes of runtests

     System.getProperty("user.dir"); ==>
     (C:/Users/drysa/IdeaProjects/TestNGFrameworkNew) = returns directory path from which JMV gets executed